MZK 2024-07-15 22:26:34-04:00 - build 6347

1. If Hex View of the Internal Viewer is wider than the window, it can be properly
   scrolled horizontally with arrow keys. (The width of the Hex View depends only
   on the number of bytes per line and does not change with the Far window width.)

2. Ctrl+Alt+Arrow keys snap the number of bytes per line in Hex View of the
   Internal Viewer to the multiples of 16 (instead of changing the number by 16).

3. Help files updated accordingly.

4. Refactoring

